        "numero": 1,
        "texte": "Déterminer la droite de Mayer.",
        "niveau": "medium",
        "reponse": "<p><strong>Groupe 1 :</strong> \(A(1,1)\), \(B(2,3)\) (2 premiers points).</p><p>\(G_1(\\bar{x}_1, \\bar{y}_1) = \\left(\\dfrac{1+2}{2}, \\dfrac{1+3}{2}\\right) = (1,5; 2)\).</p><p><strong>Groupe 2 :</strong> \(D(4,6)\), \(E(5,5)\) (2 derniers points).</p><p>\(G_2(\\bar{x}_2, \\bar{y}_2) = \\left(\\dfrac{4+5}{2}, \\dfrac{6+5}{2}\\right) = (4,5; 5,5)\).</p><p><strong>Droite de Mayer :</strong> \(a = \\dfrac{5,5 - 2}{4,5 - 1,5} = \\dfrac{3,5}{3} = \\dfrac{7}{6} \\approx 1,17\).</p><p>\(b = 2 - \\dfrac{7}{6} \\times 1,5 = 2 - \\dfrac{7}{4} = \\dfrac{1}{4} = 0,25\).</p><p>Équation : \(y = \\dfrac{7}{6}x + \\dfrac{1}{4}\).</p>",
